  - Sets status=stopped in state.json
  - DELETES the Discord thread entirely (requires Manage Threads perm)
  - Worktree, branch, logs all preserved on disk
  - Falls back to a farewell post if thread deletion fails

Permission model (enforced when called by an agent):
  - An agent can only kill itself or agents in its own subtree
  - CLI caller (human, no $C3R_AGENT_NAME) can kill anyone

To fully wipe an agent including worktree + branch, see `c3r reset`.
